Audacity Quickstart: Podcast with Intro/Outro Music

Step 1: Import Your Files

  1. Split the track in two (so you can use the beginning as the intro, and the end as the outro):
    • Click the Selection Tool (top-left)
    • Select the first ~15 seconds of the music waveform
    • Press Ctrl+C to copy
    • Go to Tracks Add New Stereo Track, then paste (Ctrl+V)
    • Do the same with the last 15 seconds of the music paste to another new stereo track

  • Your voice track
  • Intro music track
  • Outro music track

Step 3: Arrange the Timeline

  1. Move the voice track slightly forward so it starts after the intro music
    Use the Time Shift Tool ( icon)

  2. Move the outro music to the very end of the voice track

  3. Adjust volume
    Use the Gain slider on the left of each track to lower music volume beneath your voice

  4. Fade In/Fade Out music

    • Select the first few seconds of the intro music Effect Fade In
    • Select the last few seconds of the outro music Effect Fade Out

Step 4: Export Your Episode

  1. Go to File Export Export as MP3
  2. Choose a filename like:
    Episode_0_The_Voice_Within.mp3
  3. Bitrate: 128 kbps or higher is good
  4. Add metadata if prompted (title, artist, etc.)
